        "text": "This document page from the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. Market Monitoring Unit report focuses on the SPP market footprint and its participants as of the end of 2017.\n\nKey points include:\n\n1. **SPP Market Footprint and ISO/RTO Operating Regions**:\n   - The page features two maps:\n     - The first map highlights the SPP market footprint in red, covering states including North Dakota, South Dakota, Nebraska, Kansas, Oklahoma, Texas, Arkansas, and parts of surrounding states.\n     - The second map shows various ISO (Independent System Operator) and RTO (Regional Transmission Organization) operating regions across the United States and parts of Canada, including entities like California ISO, Midcontinent ISO, PJM Interconnection, New York ISO, and others.\n\n2. **SPP Market Participants**:\n   - At the end of 2017, there were 211 entities participating in the SPP Integrated Marketplace.\n   - These participants fall into several categories:\n     - Regulated investor-owned utilities\n     - Electric cooperatives\n     - Municipal utilities\n     - Federal and state agencies\n     - Independent power producers\n     - Financial-only market participants who do not own physical assets\n   - The document references Figure 2-2 (not shown on this page), which details the distribution of the 61 resource owners registered to participate in the Integrated Marketplace.\n\nOverall, the page provides an overview of the geographic scope of the SPP market and the diversity of its participants within the integrated electricity marketplace as of 2017.",
